comment: Induction in a monoid. In this theorem, ` ps ( x ) ` is the "generic" proposition to be be proved (the first four hypotheses tell its values at y, y+z, 0, A respectively). The two induction hypotheses mndind.i1 and mndind.i2 tell that it is true at 0, that if it is true at y then it is true at y+z (provided z is in ` G ` ). The hypothesis mndind.k tells that ` G ` is generating. (Contributed by SO, 14-Jul-2018.)
